    • CompareValue

      public int CompareValue(Object obj)
      Description: Compares two cards and returns the difference between the hierarchy value of their values. If a card value is worth more than the other then his hierarchy value is bigger. For instance, an Ace is worth more than a King, hence, the Ace hierarchy value (13) is bigger than the King hierarchy value (12).
      Specified by:
      CompareValue in interface ICard
      Parameters:
      obj - (Object) - Object that will be compared with the object that called this method
